message.content:
1. There are 40 patients with chronic whiplash syndrome.
2. The patients have whiplash associated disorders grade 1 and 2.
3. The patients were randomly assigned to receive treatments.
4. One group of patients was assigned to receive botulinum toxin.
5. The maximum dosage of botulinum toxin given was 100 units.
6. Another group of patients was assigned to receive a placebo.
7. The placebo given was saline.
8. The treatments were administered in muscles with increased tenderness.

messages.content:
Statement: 40 patients with chronic whiplash syndrome (whiplash associated disorders grade 1 and 2) were randomly assigned to receive botulinum toxin (maximum 100 units) or placebo (saline) in muscles with increased tenderness.
